post_text: CALENDAR UPDATE: School starts Monday August 24th. The board approved a professional learning day for all staff August 28 so there will be NO SCHOOL FOR STUDENTS on August 28.
text: CALENDAR UPDATE: School starts Monday August 24th. The board approved a professional learning day for all staff August 28 so there will be NO SCHOOL FOR STUDENTS on August 28.

post_text:
School starts on Monday, August 24th. If you haven’t registered your student online to attend classes, please do so as soon as possible. If your child is going to do remote learning, please call 970-563-0500.
If your child will be riding a bus, please call the transportation department at 970-563-4216 so they can be put on the route. Visit the website for detailed letters regarding Back to School and transportation changes.

post_text: The School District has recently become aware that there was a positive CoVid test of a family member of a high school female athlete who has been attending the summer workouts. The family is in self quarantine and at this time, no other family members have shown symptoms. The athlete only participated in the practices that occurred outside and were without physical contact. The High School has decided to cancel the volleyball and girls basketball summer workouts until further notice as a precautionary measure. High School families have been notified of potential exposure so that parents can keep a close eye on their children. The Ignacio School District is taking this news very seriously and we will keep the community posted as we work through this situation.

post_text:
There are several National Groups encouraging people to “adopt” a 2020 Senior, mentor them, send small gifts of their favorites, send encouraging messages and just support these young men and women during this time of missing out on what they have worked 12 years for. I was added to a group, adopted a few great girls, and then thought - why not do this for just our local grads. Support our own community - so here we go ~

For all the parents with graduation seniors, send out the announcements and celebrate their accomplishments ! Most of these students were also born during 9/11 era - they can handle this.

Bullet Point Instructions
** Parents - post your grad (or grads post your own)…

post_text:
Update on school closure.
Yesterday Governor Polis held a news conference to lift some of the stay at home restrictions. He changed it to "Safer at home". Some businesses will be re-opening on limited basis.
Regarding schools, they will remain closed for the rest of the year. This mandate was confirmed by both Governor Polis and Commissioner Anthes during this morning conference call.

Ignacio School District will continue with online teaching for the rest of the year.

More details will follow as we keep developing plans to continue with this process.

Thank you
Rocco
